e%20Cinematograph%20(Certification)%20Rules%2C%202024%2C%20is%20now%20in%20place%2C%20instead%20of%20the%201983%20version.%20The%20government%20also%20amended%20the%20Cinematograph%20Act%2C%201952.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBFC%20(Central%20Board%20of%20Film%20Certification)%20introduced%20an%20updated%20film%20certification%20system%20aligned%20with%20social%20values%20and%20promoting%20age-appropriate%20viewing.%20The%20rules%20were%20substantially%20overhauled%20to%20improve%2C%20update%20and%20modernise%20the%20entire%20process%20of%20certification%20of%20films%20for%20public%20viewing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20updated%20certification%20system%20became%20effective%20on%20October%2024%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20explain%20the%20changes%20to%20a%20wide%20cross-section%20of%20viewers%20and%20to%20all%20filmmakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20film%20industry%20is%20the%20largest%20in%20the%20world%2C%20just%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20sheer%20number%20of%20films%20produced%20-%20more%20than%202200%20films%20annually.%20However%2C%20the%20revenue%20earned%20by%20the%20Indian%20film%20industry%20is%20smaller%20in%20comparison%20to%20other%20film%20industries%20in%20the%20world%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20cheap%20tickets%20and%20piracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20age-based%20categories%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20revamped%20rules%2C%20new%20categories%20for%20age%20groups%20were%20introduced.%20Existing%20categories%20were%20split%20into%20sub-categories.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20UA%20category%20was%20divided%20into%20three%20age-based%20categories%3A%20seven%20years%20(UA%207%2B)%2C%20thirteen%20years%20(UA%2013%2B)%2C%20and%20sixteen%20years%20(UA%2016%2B)%2C%20instead%20of%20the%20earlier%20twelve%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20age-based%20ratings%20%26quot%3Bwould%20be%20only%20recommendatory%2C%20meant%20for%20the%20parents%20or%20guardians%20to%20consider%20whether%20their%20children%20should%20view%20such%20a%20film%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERules%20for%20certifying%20films%20are%20formulated%20under%20the%20Cinematograph%20Act%2C%201952%20(Act%2037).%20In%20the%20beginning%2C%20there%20were%20just%20two%20categories%3A%20U%20(meant%20for%20unrestricted%20public%20exhibition)%20and%20A%20(restricted%20to%20adult%20audiences%2C%20but%20nudity%20was%20not%20allowed).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20more%20categories%20were%20added%20in%20June%2C%201983%20-%20UA%20(unrestricted%20public%20exhibition%20subject%20to%20parental%20guidance%20for%20children%20below%20the%20age%20of%20twelve)%20and%20'S'%20(restricted%20to%20specialised%20audiences%20such%20as%20doctors%20or%20scientists).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20age%20limit%20was%20earlier%20set%20at%2012%20years%2C%20but%20in%20the%20latest%20amendment%20carried%20out%20in%202023%2C%20this%20was%20further%20refined%20and%20sub-classified%20into%207%2C%2013%20and%2016%20years%20of%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20presumed%20that%20the%20parents%20shall%20be%20motivated%20to%20analyse%20and%20study%20each%20film's%20details%20and%20consider%20their%20child's%20temperament%20before%20allowing%20them%20to%20watch.%20The%20updated%20guidelines%20aim%20to%20foster%20transparency%20and%20ensure%20that%20films%20are%20properly%20classified%20for%20modern%20audiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20was%20it%20needed%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20newly-added%20sub-classification%20has%20been%20made%20to%20help%20parents%20make%20an%20informed%20choice%20about%20what%20content%20is%20appropriate%20for%20their%20children%2C%20in%20view%20of%20factors%20like%20violence%2C%20intimacy%2C%20horror%2C%20or%20mature%20themes.%20The%20'UA'%20categories%20now%20define%20the%20intensity%20of%20these%20elements%2C%20with%20age-specific%20markers%2C%20offering%20parents%20a%20better%20understanding%20of%20the%20content's%20suitability%20for%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20need%20for%20introducing%20more%20age%20categories%2C%20TS%20Nagabharana%2C%20member%20of%20the%20CBFC%20(Central%20Board%20of%20Film%20Certification)%20or%20Censor%20Board%2C%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20thinking%20at%20least%20in%20the%20CBFC%20has%20been%20there%20for%20a%20long%20time%20to%20introduce%20new%20age%20categories.%20Until%20now%2C%20it%20was%20all%20left%20on%20the%20adult's%20guidance%20for%20the%20underage.%20This%20new%20arrangement%20will%20help%20the%20certifying%20committee%20avoid%20placing%20all%20films%20under%20just%20one%20category.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3BBefore%20deciding%20these%20categories%2C%20many%20things%20were%20discussed.%20For%20instance%2C%20sometimes%20certain%20content%20with%20violence%20is%20thought%20to%20be%20permissible%20for%2016-year-olds%2C%20but%20not%20for%20seven-year-olds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeveloped%20countries%20like%20the%20US%20and%20UK%20also%20have%20defined%20film%20ratings%20for%20children%20and%20young%20adults%2C%20and%20the%20CBFC%20studied%20them%20before%20upgrading%20India's%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20social%20media%20and%20online%20streaming%20platforms%20such%20as%20Netflix%20and%20Amazon%20Prime%20etc%2C%20children%20and%20teenagers%20can%20freely%20access%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20uncensored%20exposure%20to%20violence%2C%20sexually%20explicit%20content%20and%20abusive%20language%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20led%20to%20many%20behavioural%20issues%20in%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20is%20also%20mindful%20of%20the%20unhindered%20access%20of%20children%20to%20varied%20content%20online%20through%20digital%20media.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20regulatory%20body%20to%20monitor%20content%2C%20it%20is%20the%20parents%20who%20have%20to%20be%20watchful%20and%20alert.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20unhampered%20viewing%20has%20negatively%20impacted%20younger%20minds%20now.%20So%2C%20through%20this%20new%20age%20rating%20system%2C%20we%20want%20to%20develop%20self-discipline%20among%20both%20parents%20and%20children%20about%20what%20they%20should%20be%20watching%20and%20what%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Nagabharana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20filmmakers%20now%20know%20what%20target%20audience%20they%20are%20making%20films%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20censor%20board's%20move%20highlights%20the%20growing%20importance%20of%20age-appropriate%20viewing%20experiences%20for%20children%2C%20while%20empowering%20parents%20to%20make%20better%20choices%20with%20varied%20social%20and%20digital%20media%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEducation%20and%20visual%20literacy%20are%20needed%20to%20evaluate%20online%20information%20critically.%20Sadly%2C%20in%20our%20country%2C%20a%20large%20section%20of%20the%20population%20still%20prefers%20mobile%20phones%20over%20quality%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20complaints%20of%20the%20audiences%20and%20the%20filmmakers%20about%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20censor%20board%20in%20the%20past%20have%20been%20addressed%20by%20the%20government%20through%20the%20amendment%20in%20the%20Act.%20It%20will%20be%20good%20for%20the%20board%20and%20the%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20ministry%20to%20raise%20awareness%20among%20viewers%20and%20filmmakers%20about%20the%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732881960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2018-04%2Ftv-generic-pixabay_650x400_41524915840.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fanalysis-censor-boards-new-age-based-categories-need-to-be-popularised-7134238%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20has%20been%20more%20than%20eight%20months%20since%20the%20Centre%20updated%20its%20film%20certification%20rules%20and%20replaced%20a%2040-year-old%20law%20to%20tackle%20issues%20such%20as%20age-appropriate%20viewing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fanalysis-censor-boards-new-age-