%20and%20influencer%2C%20revealed%20her%20remarkable%20%2443.4%20million%20earnings%20from%20OnlyFans%2C%20surpassing%20NBA%20star%20Jayson%20Tatums%20%2435%20million%20salary.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fsophie-rain-this-adult-star-earns-rs-360-crore-annually-surpassing-nba-superstars-earnings-7133564%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20Big%20Bulldozer%20Verdict%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20To%20Examine%20UP%20Gangster%20Act%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20agreed%20to%20examine%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Gangsters%20and%20Anti-Social%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%2C%201986.%20This%20comes%20just%2016%20days%20after%20the%20same%20bench%20issued%20nationwide%20guidelines%20prohibiting%20illegal%20demolitions%20of%20properties%20linked%20to%20accused%20persons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20BR%20Gavai%20and%20KV%20Viswanathan%20issued%20notice%20to%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20government%20in%20response%20to%20a%20petition%20filed%20through%20advocate%20Ansar%20Ahmed%20Chaudhary.%20The%20petition%20challenges%20Sections%203%2C%2012%2C%20and%2014%20of%20the%20Act%20under%20the%202021%20regulations%20that%20govern%20the%20registration%20of%20cases%2C%20property%20attachment%2C%20investigation%2C%20and%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20argues%20that%20the%20Act%20violates%20fundamental%20rights%20by%20allowing%20the%20government%20to%20act%20as%20complainant%2C%20prosecutor%2C%20and%20adjudicator.%20Among%20the%20contested%20provisions%2C%20Rule%2022%20permits%20filing%20an%20FIR%20based%20on%20a%20single%20act%20or%20omission%2C%20making%20the%20accused's%20criminal%20history%20irrelevant.%20The%20petition%20claims%20this%20undermines%20due%20process%20and%20breaches%20protections%20under%20Article%2020(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20added%20that%20provisions%20under%20the%20Act%20also%20enable%20the%20government%20to%20confiscate%20entire%20properties%20without%20adequate%20judicial%20oversight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20November%2013%20verdict%20addressing%20the%20misuse%20of%20bulldozer%20actions%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20that%20executive%20overreach%20in%20demolishing%20properties%20of%20accused%20persons%20violates%20the%20principles%20of%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20executive%20body%20cannot%20act%20as%20a%20judge%20to%20punish%20an%20individual%20by%20demolishing%20properties%2C%20especially%20without%20following%20due%20process.%20Such%20actions%20are%20arbitrary%20and%20unconstitutional%2C%20the%20bench%20observed.%20The%20court%20said%20that%20punitive%20demolitions%20without%20trial%20recall%20%26quot%3Blawless%20state%20affairs%26quot%3B%20where%20%26quot%3Bmight%20is%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnly%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20accusations%2C%20if%20the%20executive%20demolishes%20the%20property%2Fproperties%20of%20such%20an%20accused%20person%20without%20following%20the%20due%20process%20of%20law%2C%20it%20would%20strike%20at%20the%20basic%20principle%20of%20rule%20of%20law%20and%20is%20not%20permissible%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said%20in%20its%2095-page%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20executive%20cannot%20become%20a%20judge%20and%20decide%20that%20a%20person%20accused%20is%20guilty%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20punish%20him%20by%20demolishing%20his%20residential%2Fcommercial%20property%2Fproperties.%20Such%20an%20act%20of%20the%20executive%20would%20be%20transgressing%20its%20limits%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20said%20the%20principle%20that%20%26quot%3Ban%20accused%20is%20not%20guilty%20unless%20proven%20so%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law%26quot%3B%20is%20foundational%20to%20any%20legal%20system.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22pub